\boxed{Robert Venturi}

Robert Venturi designed the **Langston Hughes Barn** in Clinton, Tennessee, as part of his experimental **"Vanna Venturi House" project** (though the barn was a later addition). This work reflects his postmodern approach, blending vernacular and modernist forms. The barn was a playful homage to Hughes’s rural roots and Venturi’s interest in American folk architecture.
